0any%20more%20appropriate%20term%20for%20some%20foreign%20figures%20and%20leaders%20than%20the%20word%20bullying%20--%20insist%20on%20negotiations%2C%26quot%3B%20Khamenei%20told%20officials%20after%20Trump%20threatened%20military%20action%20if%20Iran%20refuses%20to%20engage%20in%20talks%20over%20its%20nuclear%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20negotiations%20are%20not%20aimed%20at%20solving%20problems%2C%20they%20aim%20at%20domination%2C%26quot%3B%20Khamenei%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Trump%20said%20he%20had%20written%20to%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%2C%20urging%20new%20talks%20on%20the%20country's%20nuclear%20programme%20or%20face%20possible%20military%20action%20if%20it%20refuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhamenei%20said%20on%20Saturday%20that%20bullying%20powers%20aim%20to%20assert%20their%20own%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20setting%20new%20expectations%20that%20they%20think%20will%20definitely%20not%20be%20met%20by%20Iran%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20without%20naming%20the%20United%20States%20or%20referring%20to%20Trump's%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Foreign%20Minister%20Abbas%20Araghchi%20told%20AFP%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20Tehran%20would%20not%20negotiate%20under%20%26quot%3Bmaximum%20pressure%26quot%3B%2C%20although%20he%20did%20not%20directly%20address%20Trump's%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20reinstated%20his%20policy%20from%20his%20first%20term%20of%20maximum%20pressure%20on%20Iran%20upon%20returning%20to%20the%20White%20House%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20this%20policy%2C%20the%20United%20States%20in%202018%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Iran%20nuclear%20accord%20formally%20known%20as%20the%20Joint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(JCPOA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20JCPOA%2C%20set%20between%20Tehran%20and%20western%20powers%20in%202015%2C%20had%20offered%20relief%20from%20economic%20sanctions%20in%20exchange%20for%20limits%20on%20Iran's%20nuclear%20activ