eapons%20to%2031%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20in%202023%2C%20that%20number%20had%20fallen%20to%2012%2C%20according%20to%20SIRPI.%20This%20is%20a%20function%20of%20supply%20chains%20and%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20purchase%20of%20weapons%20is%20often%20a%20statement%20of%20alignment%2C%20several%20countries%20who%20used%20to%20buy%20Russian%20arms%20have%20turned%20to%20Western%2C%20domestic%2C%20or%20other%20alternatives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20due%20to%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russia%2C%20maintaining%20Russian%20weapons%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20difficult%20for%20buyers.%20Therefore%2C%20to%20safeguard%20themselves%20from%20uncertain%20maintenance%2C%20countries%20are%20seeking%20safer%20sellers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Asia%20and%20Oceania%2C%20which%20had%20accounted%20for%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20overall%20Russian%20weapons%20exports%20between%202018%20and%202023%2C%20the%20US%20is%20now%20the%20biggest%20seller.%20And%20in%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20where%20Russia%20used%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20seller%2C%20the%20number%20one%20spot%20is%20now%20held%20by%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BRussia's%20arms%20export%20categories%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20%5Bhave%20mainly%5D%20included%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20combat%20aircraft%2Fhelicopters%20and%20their%20parts%20(including%20engines)%2C%20and%20some%20naval%20systems%20like%20diesel-electric%20submarines%2C%20corvettes%20and%20anti-ship%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20Luzin%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20visiting%20scholar%20at%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20of%20Law%20and%20Diplomacy%20at%20Tufts%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20weapons%2C%20however%2C%20have%20been%20far%20from%20excellent%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResearch%20published%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinte